What Claude SEO Pro adds on top of upstream
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. onboarding/ - a guided, secure API onboarding system (DataForSEO,
   Google APIs, Firecrawl, Exa) with live validation, owner-only credential
   storage under ~/.config/claude-seo/, and safe-merge MCP configuration.
2. skills/seo-setup/ - a /seo-setup Claude Code skill that drives guided
   installation and onboarding conversationally.
3. skills/seo-audit/SKILL.md - the Evidence Integrity Protocol (anti-
   fabrication rules) and a fix to the shared-script fetch path so audit
   subagents reliably read pre-fetched evidence instead of guessing.
4. Self-contained installers (install.ps1 / install.sh) that install from
   this repository directly and launch onboarding.

These additions are likewise MIT-licensed. See LICENSE.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party APIs and MCP servers
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
This software can configure and call third-party services that require the
user's own accounts and credentials, each under its own terms of service:
DataForSEO, Google APIs (PageSpeed Insights, CrUX, Search Console, GA4),
Firecrawl, and Exa. No credentials are bundled with this software. Users
are responsible for their own API usage and costs.
